criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Outpatients aged 18 to 45 years;

          -  Diagnoses of BPD according to Diagnostic and Statistical Manual for Mental Disorders
             (4th version Revised) (DSM-IV-TR) criteria and evaluated by two semi-structured
             diagnostic interviews

          -  Structured Clinical Interview for DSM-IV Axis II Disorders (SCID-II) and the Revised
             Diagnostic Interview for Borderlines (DIB-R)

          -  Clinical severity measured with Clinical Global Impression for BPD (CGI-BPD) higher
             than 4;

          -  Functional impairment measured with a Global Assessment Functioning (GAF) lower than
             65.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  No severe physical conditions, such as organic brain syndrome or neurological disease
             that could affect neuropsychological performance;

          -  Intelligence Quotient (IQ) < 85;

          -  Major Depression Disorder (MDD) or substance misuse within the last 6 months;

          -  Schizophrenia, severe psychotic disorder or bipolar disorder;

          -  Previous participation in any psychoeducation or cognitive rehabilitation
             intervention.
